The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 23 October is 704,443 (1,251.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 October, there were 101,605 new confirmed cases (180.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 October, there were 91,473 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 11% (10,132 extra cases).
